    "name": "Letterman Buildout Orders",
    "description": "# Letterman Buildout Orders API Documentation\n\nAPI endpoints for managing newsletter buildout orders, including order listing, state management, phase transitions, and step updates.\n\n## Authentication\n\nAll endpoints require Bearer token authentication. Include the token in the `Authorization` header:\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}\n```\n\n## Base URL\n\n```\nhttps://api.letterman.ai/api\n```\n\n## Rate Limiting\n\nAPI requests are subject to rate limiting. Please refer to the response headers for current limits.\n\n## Support\n\nFor API support, please contact the Letterman development team.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "13141272"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Buildout Orders",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get Order States",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/buildout-orders/get-states",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["buildout-orders", "get-states"]
            },
            "description": "# Get Order States\n\nRetrieves aggregated counts of orders in DRAFT or PENDING state for each step per phase.\n\n## Endpoint\n\n`GET /buildout-orders/get-states`\n\n## Authentication\n\n**Required** - Bearer token in Authorization header\n\n## Response Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Description |\n|-------|------|-------------|\n| `phase1` | object | Counts for Phase 1 steps |\n| `phase1.step1` | number | Count of pending Phase 1 Step 1 orders |\n| `phase1.step2` | number | Count of pending Phase 1 Step 2 orders |\n| `phase1.step3` | number | Count of pending Phase 1 Step 3 orders |\n| `phase2` | object | Counts for Phase 2 steps |\n| `phase2.step1` | number | Count of pending Phase 2 Step 1 orders |\n| `phase2.step2` | number | Count of pending Phase 2 Step 2 orders |\n| `hasPendingPhase1Order` | boolean | Whether any Phase 1 orders are pending |\n| `hasPendingPhase2Order` | boolean | Whether any Phase 2 orders are pending |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "Get Order States",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/buildout-orders/get-states", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["buildout-orders", "get-states"]}
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}],
              "cookie": [],
              "body": "{\n    \"data\": {\n        \"phase1\": {\n            \"step1\": 3,\n            \"step2\": 2,\n            \"step3\": 1\n        },\n        \"phase2\": {\n            \"step1\": 2,\n            \"step2\": 1\n        },\n        \"hasPendingPhase1Order\": true,\n        \"hasPendingPhase2Order\": true\n    }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "List Orders",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}",
                "type": "text"
              }
            ],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/buildout-orders?phase={{phase}}&step={{step}}&show_completed={{showCompleted}}&state={{state}}&search={{search}}",
              "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"],
              "path": ["buildout-orders"],
              "query": [
                {"key": "phase", "value": "{{phase}}", "description": "Phase filter (PHASE_1, PHASE_2). Default: PHASE_1"},
                {"key": "step", "value": "{{step}}", "description": "Step filter (NEW_ORDER, STEP_1, STEP_2, STEP_3). Default: NEW_ORDER"},
                {"key": "show_completed", "value": "{{showCompleted}}", "description": "Show completed orders (true/false)"},
                {"key": "state", "value": "{{state}}", "description": "Filter by state"},
                {"key": "search", "value": "{{search}}", "description": "Search term"}
              ]
            },
            "description": "# List Orders\n\nRetrieves buildout orders filtered by phase and step.\n\n## Endpoint\n\n`GET /buildout-orders`\n\n## Authentication\n\n**Required** - Bearer token in Authorization header\n\n## Query Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Type | Required | Default | Description |\n|-----------|------|----------|---------|-------------|\n| `phase` | string | No | PHASE_1 | Phase filter (PHASE_1, PHASE_2) |\n| `step` | string | No | NEW_ORDER | Step filter (NEW_ORDER, STEP_1, STEP_2, STEP_3) |\n| `show_completed` | string | No | false | Show completed orders (true/false) |\n| `state` | string | No | - | Filter by state |\n| `search` | string | No | - | Search term |\n\n## Phase & Step Combinations\n\n| Phase | Available Steps |\n|-------|----------------|\n| PHASE_1 | NEW_ORDER, STEP_1, STEP_2, STEP_3 |\n| PHASE_2 | NEW_ORDER, STEP_1, STEP_2 |"
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "List Orders",
              "originalRequest": {
                "method": "GET",
                "header": [{"key": "Authorization", "value": "Bearer {{accessToken}}", "type": "text"}],
                "url": {"raw": "{{baseUrl}}/buildout-orders?phase=PHASE_1&step=NEW_ORDER", "host": ["{{baseUrl}}"], "path": ["buildout-orders"], "query": [{"key": "phase", "value": "PHASE_1"}, {"key": "step", "value": "NEW_ORDER"}]}
              },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "_postman_previewlanguage": "json",
              "header": [{"key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json; charset=utf-8"}],
              "cookie": [],
              "body": "{\n    \"data\": {\n        \"orders\": []\n    }\n}"
            }
          ]
        },
